<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-01-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-01-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="37" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d37">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 836/86.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Ambassador <persName type="to">Dudley</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-01-15"><hi rend="italic">January 15,
                                1908</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Bacon states that the department assumes that the decree signed by
                            President of Brazil on the 11th instant puts reduction of 20 per cent in
                            force retroactively as from January 1, and asks if this is correct.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>